== Features ==

* Build of [http://searle.x10host.com/z80/SimpleZ80.html Grant Searles's Simple Z80 CPU]
** Runs BASIC
* [https://github.com/douggilliland/Retro-Computers/blob/master/Z80/Parts/Z80%20Family/Z80%20CPU%20z80b8400.pdf Z80 CPU]
* 7.3728 MHz clock
* [https://github.com/land-boards/lb-boards/blob/master/RetroCPUs/SIMPLE-Z80/PARTS/TC551001_128KB_SRAM_datasheet.pdf 56KB SRAM (uses 128KB parts)]
* [https://github.com/douggilliland/Retro-Computers/blob/master/Z80/Parts/EEPROMs/EEPROM%2028C64.pdf 8KB EPROM/EEPROM]
* [https://github.com/land-boards/lb-boards/blob/master/RetroCPUs/SIMPLE-Z80/PARTS/MC68B50_43633.pdf 68B50 Serial Port (ACIA)]
** [https://github.com/land-boards/lb-boards/blob/master/RetroCPUs/SIMPLE-6502/PARTS/max232.pdf RS-232 port]
** Header for FTDI
** 115,200 baud
* Reset switch with [https://github.com/land-boards/lb-boards/blob/master/RetroCPUs/SIMPLE-6502/PARTS/ds1813-maxim%20integrated%20products_1178753.pdf optional DS1813 Power Supervisor]
* 95x95mm card
* (4) 6-32 mounting holes

=== Memory Map ===

* 0x0000-0x1FFF 8KB ROM
* 0x2000-0xFFFF 56KB SRAM
* I/O
** 0x00-0x7F - Free
** 0x80-0x81 - Serial port (ACIA)

